H3.text: From which European country does Limburger cheese originate. Beljum

A4.text: Limburger, commonly known as Limburg (in southern Dutch contexts Rommedoe, and in Belgium Herve cheese), is a cheese that originated in the Herve area of the historical Duchy of Limburg, which had its capital in Limbourg-sur-Vesdre, now in the French‑speaking Belgian province of Liège.

A5.text: Herve is a Belgian rind washed soft cheese made from raw cow's milk.
